{
  "_comment": "Radar room-based objective targets (area-id -> [{name, rooms, count}]). Derived from Radar targets.json entries with Name '*' + a Rooms filter (the room filter the Radar.ClusterTarget bridge DROPS, so StepTargetResolver matches these against IngameState.Data.AreaGraphs room names directly). 'name' = Radar DisplayName; the resolver joins it to a route step when a significant name word (>=4 ch, not a generic stoplist word) appears in the step text. 'rooms' = room-name substrings (the '*' wildcards stripped). Used for an on-the-ground objective whose entity isn't a standard interactable (e.g. g1_5 'Obelisk of Rust' which loads as an IngameIcon). Optional 'progressFlags' (harvested, ordered): per-sub-objective QuestFlags that flip one at a time as you complete each (e.g. the 3 Rust obelisks). When one flips true the pathing drops the path to whichever objective room is nearest the player at that instant, leaving lines only to the not-yet-done ones.",
